UK: LME copper slips in late trading.LME copper slips in late trading.LME copper edged down in late inter-office trading after losing ground most of the day.At 1800 GMT, three months copper was indicated at $1,926/29 per tonne compared to a afternoon kerb closing of $1,931.On Monday copper closed the kerb at $1,942.After the end of Tuesday's kerb, copper drifted a few dollars higher, but quickly lost heart and slid back.Analysts said copper was looking weak and may be moving towards a test of the bottom end of its $1,900-1,970 range.Aluminium and the other metals were little changed.--London Newsroom +44 171 542 8065